<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 3:00PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Bedford County through 330 PM EDT...
At 300 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Sedalia, or 8 miles north of Bedford, moving east at 5 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Big Island...
Sedalia...
Coleman Falls...
and Snowden.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
